23/09/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- One Romanian soldier was killed and five were injured on Friday (September 21st) in a roadside blast in southeastern Iraq. 
Romania has 498 troops in the country, most of whom are deployed to patrolling and humanitarian missions. 
Earlier this month, a Romanian soldier was killed and four were wounded in Afghanistan after their vehicle hit an improvised bomb. 
(Rompres, AP, AFP, Hotnews.ro - 21/09/07)
